<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Likely1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Likely,</orth> adj. 1) probable: <cit><quote>in l. thoughts the other kills thee quickly,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 990" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 990</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this is most l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 103</bibl></cit>; <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 1, 40</bibl>; <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 68</bibl>; <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 135</bibl>. <cit><quote>I never thought it possible or l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 154</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. peril,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.184" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 184</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a l. guess,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.207" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 207</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. wars,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a l. piece of work,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 156</bibl></cit>. <emph>it is l.,</emph> followed by a clause: <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 4, 16</bibl>. Used personally, with an inf.: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.171" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.188" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.74" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.5.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 5, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.209" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 209</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.35" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.35" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 35</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.408" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 408</bibl>.<lb />2) having a certain air, expressive: <cit><quote>never saw I figures so l. to report themselves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 83</bibl></cit>.
